# Git: no automatic push

**Do not** commit or push to `origin` unless the user **explicitly** asks to upload, commit, push, or ship changes to git.

When they do ask: review `git status`, stage relevant paths, commit with a clear message, and push (unless they said commit-only or there are secrets in the diff). If push fails, report the error and what was committed locally.

If the user later opts back into “push after substantive work,” they can say so and this rule can be updated.
